    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Earthenware tile of Spanish or Portuguese manufacture, painted and enameled in rich colors. They are typically large and used to decorate the exterior walls of buildings. The term is probably of Arabic origin but its derivation is debated.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
